<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="582" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,1059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,186,209]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is from the Latin for “two spotted” and refers to the two brownish pigmented spots on each wing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="582" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,1059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,256,279]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[628,804,255,279]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conglomerata">
<emphasis box="[628,650,256,279]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[664,804,255,279]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">conglomerata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in terms of two wing-spots. It can be distinguished from the latter in: (
<number box="[249,259,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
) Costa long (costal index about 
<number box="[584,631,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="0.61">0.61</number>
), and the latter Costa shorter (costal index about 
<number box="[1118,1222,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="0.435" valueMax="0.44" valueMin="0.43">0.43–0.44</number>
). (
<number box="[1246,1260,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.0">2</number>
) wing with a big, diamond, brownish pigmented spot between the apex of vein R 
<number box="[788,795,340,352]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[803,809,340,352]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="5.0">5</number>
and the middle of vein M 
<number box="[1071,1078,340,352]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
, and the spot is inclined 
<number box="[1327,1353,325,348]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="45.0">45</number>
degrees with costa; and a small wedge-shape brown pigmented spot between the middle of veins M 
<number box="[1066,1073,378,390]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
and M 
<number box="[1142,1149,378,390]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.0">2</number>
. And in the latter, wing with an oblong brownish spot on anterior margin above apex of M 
<number box="[786,793,415,427]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
vein, and a rounded brown patch between apex of M 
<number box="[1347,1354,415,427]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
and M 
<number box="[1429,1436,415,427]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.0">2</number>
veins.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="584" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,1059]" box="[199,798,472,495]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,472,495]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Body length 
<number box="[550,581,472,495]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.9">1.9</number>
–2.0 mm (
<figureCitation box="[691,782,472,495]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,2017,2038]" captionTargetBox="[214,1372,1111,1992]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[214,1372,1111,1992]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Megaselia bisticta sp. nov. body in left lateral view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265661/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
Figure 
<number box="[769,782,472,495]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,1059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[271,366,506,529]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1906,1927]" captionTargetBox="[168,1426,211,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,194,1882]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 10. Megaselia bisticta sp. nov. 2: head; 3: fore leg; 4: mid leg; 5: hind leg; 6: wing; 7, 9: hypopygium in left lateral view; 8, 10: hypopygium in right lateral view. 3 – 6: Scale bars = 0.2 mm; 2, 7 – 10: Scale bars = 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265662/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
Figure 
<number box="[350,366,506,529]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Frons black, width about 
<quantity box="[666,752,506,529]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
, broader than height (2.0: 
<number box="[1039,1049,506,529]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
), with about 
<number box="[1194,1221,506,529]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="50.0">50</number>
hairs and a distinct median furrow. Lower supra-antennal bristles short, about 
<number box="[791,804,541,564]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[813,825,541,564]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="3.0">3</number>
as long as upper pair. Pre-ocellars slightly further from each other than upper supra-antennals. Antials closer to antero-laterals than to upper supra-antennal bristles and slightly lower than antero-laterals. Pre-ocellars nearly parallel on frons to medio-laterals and with equal distance each other. Postpedicels black or dark brown and without SPS vesicles. Arista obviously longer than frons width. Palps yellow with strong bristles which are obviously longer than maximum width of palps.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,1059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
Thorax. Thoracic dorsum black and flank dark brown. Mesopleuron with a few fine hairs. Notopleuron with 
<number box="[1422,1435,714,737]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="3.0">3</number>
bristles and no cleft. Scutellum with a pair of bristles. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[845,979,749,772]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1906,1927]" captionTargetBox="[168,1426,211,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,194,1882]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 10. Megaselia bisticta sp. nov. 2: head; 3: fore leg; 4: mid leg; 5: hind leg; 6: wing; 7, 9: hypopygium in left lateral view; 8, 10: hypopygium in right lateral view. 3 – 6: Scale bars = 0.2 mm; 2, 7 – 10: Scale bars = 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265662/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
Figures 
<number box="[938,979,749,772]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
</figureCitation>
) brown, but fore legs paler. 
<collectingCountry box="[1307,1360,749,772]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur darkened at tip. Fore metatarsus longer than joints 
<number box="[696,711,784,807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[728,741,784,807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="3.0">3</number>
. Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends 
<number box="[1195,1228,784,807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="0.6">0.6</number>
of its length. Hairs short below basal half of hind femur and anteroventral row of outer half, but the latter is longer than the former. 
<collectingCountry box="[1382,1435,818,841]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia with strong posterodorsal hairs and without anterodorsal hairs. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[990,1086,853,876]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1906,1927]" captionTargetBox="[168,1426,211,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,194,1882]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 10. Megaselia bisticta sp. nov. 2: head; 3: fore leg; 4: mid leg; 5: hind leg; 6: wing; 7, 9: hypopygium in left lateral view; 8, 10: hypopygium in right lateral view. 3 – 6: Scale bars = 0.2 mm; 2, 7 – 10: Scale bars = 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265662/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
Figure 
<number box="[1072,1086,853,876]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) nearly hyaline, with yellowish brown veins. A big diamond brownish pigmented spot is between the apex of vein R 
<number box="[1069,1077,903,915]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1085,1092,903,915]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="5.0">5</number>
and the middle of vein M 
<number box="[1376,1383,903,915]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
, and the spot is inclined 
<number box="[356,383,925,948]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="45.0">45</number>
degrees with costa; and a small wedge-shape brown pigmented spot is between the middle of veins M 
<number box="[174,181,975,987]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
and M 
<number box="[262,269,975,987]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.0">2</number>
. The area between the spots and the anterior margin of the wings is pale brown. Costal index about 
<number box="[1382,1432,960,983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="0.61">0.61</number>
. Costal ratio 
<number box="[287,327,997,1020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.6">2.6</number>
: 
<number box="[331,371,997,1020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.6">2.6</number>
: 
<number box="[375,385,997,1020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
. Costal cilia about 
<quantity box="[601,693,997,1020]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" unit="mm" value="0.07">0.07mm</quantity>
. Vein Sc runs to R 
<number box="[910,920,997,1020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
. Base of vein Rs with 
<number box="[1179,1192,997,1020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
minute hair, which is slightly shorter than vein R 
<number box="[441,449,1047,1059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[457,464,1047,1059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="3.0">3</number>
. Vein M 
<number box="[556,563,1047,1059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
obviously bent near the center. Axillary ridge with 
<number box="[1114,1127,1032,1055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="3.0">3</number>
bristles. Halteres black.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,954,2016,2038]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265661/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" targetBox="[214,1372,1111,1992]" targetPageId="1">
